# Hotkey registry

When you add a **navigable page**, **primary dashboard action**, or **top-level dialog/flow**, evaluate whether it belongs in the hotkey system.

## Register by default

Add a `HotkeyActionDef` in [`src/lib/hotkeys/actions.registry.ts`](src/lib/hotkeys/actions.registry.ts) and a default binding in [`src/lib/hotkeys/defaults.ts`](src/lib/hotkeys/defaults.ts) when:

- A new item appears in `NAV_GROUPS`, `ADMIN_LINKS`, or conditional sidebar extras.
- A trains (or similar) dashboard adds a primary officer action button.
- A global shell action should be reachable without the mouse (connect, account, reminders, etc.).

Each action needs:

- Stable `id` (e.g. `nav.members`, `trains.spinWheel`)
- `labelKey` under `hotkeys.actions.*` in `messages/en-US.json` (+ `pt-BR`)
- Correct `scope` (`global`, `page:trains`, `admin-sequence`)
- Matching `requiredPermission` (same gate as the UI control)
- Default binding that does not collide with [`src/lib/hotkeys/reserved.ts`](src/lib/hotkeys/reserved.ts) or existing defaults

Wire execution:

- **Navigation** — `href` + `kind: "navigate"` (provider handles `router.push`)
- **Page actions** — register handler via `useRegisterPageHotkeys` on the owning page
- **Admin subroutes** — `scope: "admin-sequence"` + `adminSequenceKey`

## Checklist

- [ ] New nav route → `nav.*` action (or documented skip)
- [ ] New dashboard mutation → scoped action with same permission as the button
- [ ] No binding collision with existing defaults/overrides
- [ ] Action visible in command palette and `/settings/hotkeys`
- [ ] Unit/e2e updated when default bindings change

## Explicit opt-out

Some actions must **not** be hotkeyed. Document in the PR instead of silently omitting:

- Destructive/audited flows (e.g. unlock conductor)
- Security-sensitive flows (Discord authorize, credential entry)

## Copy

User-facing hotkey labels follow [user-facing-copy-review.mdc](user-facing-copy-review.mdc): agree English in planning/review, then implement `en-US` + hand-translated `pt-BR` together.
